# iOS Foundation Template

This document defines the standard project shape to reuse when building future native iOS apps from the LoadPilot baseline.

## Goal

Use this structure when you want:
- a thin SwiftUI app target
- business logic isolated from Xcode target noise
- repeatable local builds with fewer dependency and signing regressions
- unit-testable app logic before UI iteration

## Foundation Principles

1. Keep domain logic outside the app target.
2. Treat Xcode target membership as a build-safety boundary.
3. Prefer Apple-native frameworks before adding third-party dependencies.
4. Make simulator fallbacks explicit for hardware-dependent features.
5. Keep the first version local-first unless a backend is required.
6. Add tests for parsing, workflows, and state transitions before UI polish.

